title Glowphone OS path — start with /e/OS, migrate to postmarketOS
prompt Keaton, looking at Fairphone's store (stock Android vs a pre-installed /e/OS flavour), asked whether we would have a better chance with their /e/OS or with what I had already recommended.
think read this as "better chance of what" -- and answered honestly that it depends on the goal: /e/OS is the better first chance (a real de-Googled capable phone in hand now, no flashing, bootloader kept unlockable, doors open), while postmarketOS (mainline Linux) is the better eventual substrate for a Glow-native OS down to the silicon. They are two phases, not an either/or.
think corrected my own earlier framing: GrapheneOS is Pixel-only and was never a Fairphone option, so on this device the real bases are /e/OS, CalyxOS, or postmarketOS; /e/OS is the officially-shipping de-Googled one today. Named that correction plainly rather than letting the draft's "GrapheneOS fallback" stand as if it applied to the Fairphone.
think tied the recommendation to the finishing discipline just seated: /e/OS is the "ship one real thing now" move for hardware -- live with the device this month, layer Glow surfaces as userland -- and postmarketOS is the deeper build to grow toward as it matures, exactly the ship-now-grow-later shape the counsel names.
think folded the refinement into the Glowphone doc's OS-path paragraph on the branch already pending Keaton's "send," so the pending work stays complete and honest rather than leaving the doc's recommendation stale.
obs continued to hold the send convention: this refinement is committed to the same pending branch, still not merged to main -- the merge waits for "send." Two turns now have tested the rule and honored it.
file external-research/20260715-182500_glowphone-firmware-freedom-two-body-strategy.md -- OS-path paragraph refined to the two-phase /e/OS-then-postmarketOS recommendation, with the GrapheneOS-Pixel-only correction
file session-logs/20260715-192000_glowphone-eos-vs-postmarketos-path.bron -- this log
recommend check-in -- the OS path is now honest and staged on the pending branch; it awaits Keaton's "send" to reach main, alongside the requirement refinement from the prior turn. The next real step is his word to send, or a decision to actually acquire the /e/OS Fairphone as the phase-one device.
